Sentencas: The La0.3Sr0.55Ti0.9Cr0.1O3-delta (LSTC10) anode material was synthesized by citric acid-nitrate process.
Titulo: Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell With La and Cr Co-Doped SrTiO3 as Anode

Sentencas: The yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte-supported cell was fabricated by screen printing method using LSTC10 as anode and (La0.75Sr0.25)(0.95)MnO3-delta (LSM) as cathode.
Titulo: Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell With La and Cr Co-Doped SrTiO3 as Anode

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of cell was tested by using dry hydrogen as fuel and air as oxidant in the temperature range of 800-900 degrees C. At 900 degrees C, the open circuit voltage (OCV) and the maximum power density of cell are 1.08 V and 13.0 mW.cm(-2), respectively.
Titulo: Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell With La and Cr Co-Doped SrTiO3 as Anode

Sentencas: The microstructures of cell after performance testing were investigated by scanning electron microscope (SEM).
Titulo: Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell With La and Cr Co-Doped SrTiO3 as Anode

Sentencas: The results show that the anode and cathode films are porous and closely attached to the YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell With La and Cr Co-Doped SrTiO3 as Anode

Sentencas: LSTC10 is believed to be a kind of potential solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) anode material.
Titulo: Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell With La and Cr Co-Doped SrTiO3 as Anode
